{"word":"τλήμων","slug":"τλήμων","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>τλήμων</b></el> <el>(τλήμων, <el>doric</el> <el>τλάμων, ονος, ὁ, ἡ</el>,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>*<a href='S:τλάω'><el>τλάω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>suffering, enduring, patient, stout-hearted</i>, of Ulysses, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; so <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>bold, daring, hardy, reckless</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>suffering, wretched, miserable</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <a href='S:τλημόνως'><el>τλημόνως</el></a>, <i>patiently</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div>"}]}